<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-28T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-28T06:00:00-05:00" n="308" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.97/57</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-28T11:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 29, 2
                                a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2814. For <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName>
                            from [<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_TAE1">Taylor</persName>]:</p>
                        <p>Very important to give Swiss some kind of grain until Argentine grain
                            ready, to the limitations of their tonnage. They need for the year
                            240,000 tons. Allied requirements will be reduced. Strongly urge this
                            for military reasons.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_SWG1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>